$ RMAN: command file
@ command file

An (→ development/databases/Oracle/tools/RMAN) command file stores a sequence of commands, possibly because they need to be run multiple times, perhabs on different databases.

A command file is executed with the `@` or `@@` → development/databases/Oracle/tools/RMAN/commands[commands] from the RMAN prompt or from the OS system prompt with the `@` or `CMDFILE` parameters.

{ Substitution variables

  As in → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus, there are substitution variables: `&1`, `&2`, …

  The values for the substitution variables are set from the OS command prompt like so:
code {
$ → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/bin/rman[rman] @/path/to/script/file using value_one value_two value_three …
code }


}


sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/tools/RMAN
